14:53 - Does WKHS plan to outsource production to Lordstown Motors in the future?

snippet.title: I'm Selling My Airline Stocks.. Know This Now.. Stock Market Crash.
snippet.description:
I'm Selling My Airline Stocks.. Know This Now.. Stock Market Crash. Here's a video I never expected to make in all honesty.. Since I've started posting onto youtube, it's been no secret that I'm a big bull on Airlines. But with the crazy, unprecedented time's that we're living in, things are changing.

If you enjoy the video, please drop it a like, drop me a comment letting me know what you think of the video and the new editing style and of course please subscribe if you're new around here!

Delta Airlines is currently the biggest position in my portfolio and was one of the first companies that ever got me really excited. I remember reading all of their previous quarters earnings, doing hours and hours of research and just genuinely getting excited about them. The time and effort I put into this company has served me well. I learnt how important it is to really look into a company before investing. There's much more to it than their max stock chart and their last few years revenue. 

Southwest Airlines is the other airline i'm invested in, as a more defensive investment. There's not as much buzz around them and they have in general been less volitive than the likes of American Airlines United Airlines, Spirit Airlines or DAL.

I do still love the long term outlook of these airlines if all goes well by the end of this year, but short term, they're too unpredictable to me right now.

If you enjoy the video, please drop it a like, drop me a comment letting me know what you think of the video and of course please subscribe if you're new around here!

On Thursday, The Dow Jones dropped nearly 7% in a day, The S&P 500 Nearly 6% and The NASDAQ just over 5%. A lot of people are afraid of the "Market Crash 2.0" coming and wiping away all of the profits that have been gained these last 6+ weeks.

There are a lot of new investors in the market, Robinhood has seen 300% more activity so far this year than it did at the end of 2019. With such a surge of new investors a surge in volatility was sure to follow to some extent at the very least!

I am a long term investor, so personally these red days aren't too worrying to me. They're going to happen many many times in the decades to come. Your growth stocks will lose value sometimes. snippet.title: When To Sell Your Stocks?! - Should You Sell Your Stocks Now?
snippet.description:
When To Sell Your Stocks?! - Should You Sell Your Stocks Now? In Today's video, we're taking a break from having a look for good valued stocks in the market, and we're speaking about when you should potentially sell your stocks.

If you enjoy the video, please drop it a like, drop me a comment letting me know what you think of the video and of course please subscribe if you're new around here!

Long Story short. Nobody knows. If they did, they would more than likely be the richest person in the world. But, there are some signs that indicate when you should consider selling some of your stocks, and that is what we cover in today's video

It depends on what kind of stocks you're holding for example. If you're a long term investor, you don't buy a growth stock like facebook or a dividend stock like altria with the intention of selling at a certain price.

Where as if you're buying a hype stock or a spec stock, like cll or nat you should have more on an exit plan.

snippet.title: What Are Pump And Dump Stocks? - Don't Lose Money! - NAT, CCL, VTIQ
snippet.description:
What Are Pump And Dump Stocks? - Don't Lose Money! - NAT, CCL, VTIQ. In Today's video we're speaking about Pump and Dump stocks, as I've seen a lot of people in my comment section lose a lot of money due to letting their emotions take over when it comes to these stocks with all of the hype in the world behind them.

My Full Stock Portfolio - https://www.patreon.com/jackspencerinvesting

A Pump and Dump is when a company get's a lot of hype behind it, because of media attention. historically it has been due to someone claiming they have insider information that will lead to a stock rising in price like crazy, causing other people to drive the stocks price higher, before quickly declinging.

We've seen this happen lately in regards to stocks like Nikola Motors / VTQI, NAT Stock and CCL Stock. Not to mention an awful lot of different biotech stocks.

snippet.title: The S&P 500 Explained - What is The S&P 500 Index Fund?
snippet.description:
The S&P 500 is an index fund. What is an index Fund? An index fund is a type of mutual fund with a portfolio constructed to match or track the components of a financial market index. The S&P 500 consists of 500 of the largest market cap businesses in the US. Simply put, you can buy 1 share in this index fund and invest in over 500 companies.
